WEBVTT

00:17.626 --> 00:20.542
- Uh, okay, this...

00:20.542 --> 00:22.413
Um...

00:22.413 --> 00:24.676
So...

00:24.676 --> 00:26.200
Hmm? Nah, I'm just...

00:26.200 --> 00:28.028
- You're just?
- Yeah, I'm just...

00:28.028 --> 00:30.334
I'm just--

00:30.334 --> 00:33.381
Okay, this--
this Dickinson line.

00:33.381 --> 00:38.603
"For each ecstatic instant,
we must an anguish pay

00:38.603 --> 00:42.868
in keen and quivering
ratio to the ecstasy."

00:42.868 --> 00:44.957
Oh, she's brilliant.

00:44.957 --> 00:47.482
But you're-- you're--
you're spin on this

00:47.482 --> 00:50.746
I love where...

00:50.746 --> 00:54.793
Okay. The piano wire
tight tension of the...

01:00.103 --> 01:05.717
...currency takes us years.

01:05.717 --> 01:07.154
It's so good.

01:07.154 --> 01:11.332
- You think?
- Yes. Yeah.

01:11.332 --> 01:13.421
Emily Dickinson's got nothing.

01:13.421 --> 01:14.683
Okay. No, no.

01:14.683 --> 01:16.946
You need to read more Dickinson.

01:16.946 --> 01:20.210
What is it? Something is
the thing with feathers.

01:20.210 --> 01:21.733
Something?

01:21.733 --> 01:24.345
Eric, you're missing
the most important word.

01:26.129 --> 01:28.653
- Anna?
- Partial credit.

01:33.005 --> 01:40.317
Alright, so one small moment
of joy brings the pain.

01:40.317 --> 01:44.887
One ecstatic instinct
we must an anguish to pay?

01:44.887 --> 01:47.846
I guess both.

01:47.846 --> 01:49.109
Anna?

01:49.109 --> 01:50.675
I have to go.

02:02.557 --> 02:03.906
Hey, I'll call you later.

02:03.906 --> 02:05.342
Don't-- don't--

02:10.652 --> 02:14.699
Why does Dickinson write
the word dwell in "Possibility?"

02:14.699 --> 02:17.267
Her dwell bothers me.

02:17.267 --> 02:21.576
- Hi.
- Hi.

02:21.576 --> 02:25.667
Um, I always viewed dwell
a little negatively.

02:25.667 --> 02:28.148
Possibility is there,

02:28.148 --> 02:31.803
but she doesn't leave her house,
you know?

02:31.803 --> 02:33.936
It's not
a coffee cup quote.

02:33.936 --> 02:36.634
That makes total sense.

02:36.634 --> 02:38.941
- Tea?
- No, I'm okay.

02:38.941 --> 02:45.730
Are you sure you don't want
some jasmine mint tea?

02:45.730 --> 02:48.255
Holy shit, Mom!

02:48.255 --> 02:50.996
Holy shit!
No, I knew it.

02:50.996 --> 02:52.389
I knew it when you told me
he was taking you

02:52.389 --> 02:54.217
to that ridiculous restaurant.

02:54.217 --> 02:58.265
Yeah, he did it.
And, well, I went with yes.

02:58.265 --> 03:00.180
I love this ring.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.660
It was his grandmother's.

03:02.660 --> 03:05.446
Oh, Mom,
I'm so happy for you.

03:05.446 --> 03:09.014
I'm so happy
for both you and Tim.

03:09.014 --> 03:12.235
Me, too.

03:12.235 --> 03:13.802
Wow.
- Yeah, wow!

03:18.807 --> 03:21.810
Did I overhear you
talking to a boy?

03:21.810 --> 03:23.377
I was in the hallway.

03:23.377 --> 03:26.118
Yeah.

03:26.118 --> 03:27.903
College boy?

03:30.035 --> 03:32.212
Anna?
- No, it's nothing.

03:32.212 --> 03:34.649
He lives 900 miles away.
It's nothing.

03:34.649 --> 03:36.999
Doesn't sound like nothing.

03:36.999 --> 03:39.349
Tim, get down on one knee
and all that?

03:39.349 --> 03:41.656
Nice try.
And yes, he did.

03:41.656 --> 03:43.353
It's nothing.

03:43.353 --> 03:46.400
It's just this guy
that I talked to online.

03:46.400 --> 03:49.707
I think those are literally
famous last words.

03:49.707 --> 03:52.797
Wow, so salty
now that she's engaged.

04:03.591 --> 04:06.028
I'm going to get a coffee.
Do you want one?

04:09.292 --> 04:10.989
Brit?

04:13.209 --> 04:16.604
I railed Mr. Golding
in the chem lab.

04:16.604 --> 04:19.302
He told his wife, and now we're
in a polyamorous threesome.

04:19.302 --> 04:21.652
It's great.

04:21.652 --> 04:23.915
Brit?
- Hi, sorry. What?

04:23.915 --> 04:25.308
Do you want a coffee?

04:25.308 --> 04:27.441
Uh, yeah, please. Thank you.

04:27.441 --> 04:28.964
You don't have to yell at me.

04:32.968 --> 04:36.537
Who's Eric?
- Don't answer that.

04:36.537 --> 04:38.016
Hi, Eric. Who are you?

04:38.016 --> 04:41.237
<i>Oh, um... hi.</i>

04:41.237 --> 04:42.456
Hi. Who are you?

04:42.456 --> 04:45.415
Hey, I'll call you later, okay?

04:45.415 --> 04:46.764
You can't do that.

04:46.764 --> 04:49.463
- Who's Eric?
- Not okay, Brit.

04:49.463 --> 04:51.900
You'll call him later?
That sounded like a man.

04:51.900 --> 04:54.032
What does that mean?

04:54.032 --> 04:55.425
Who is that?

04:55.425 --> 04:56.774
He's a little older.

04:56.774 --> 04:59.908
Okay.
How much older?

04:59.908 --> 05:02.519
I don't know.
College?

05:02.519 --> 05:04.216
We just talk.

05:05.914 --> 05:07.524
You're a naughty little girl,
aren't you?

05:07.524 --> 05:09.526
- Stop!
- Honey?

05:09.526 --> 05:11.876
Coming.

05:13.400 --> 05:16.968
"An old soul, having lived
through love and loss

05:16.968 --> 05:20.232
and past iterations,
sees the whole picture

05:20.232 --> 05:24.106
and is often described
as wise beyond their years."

05:26.761 --> 05:30.286
<i>See that--
that's definitely you.</i>

05:30.286 --> 05:33.333
FaceTime?

05:33.333 --> 05:37.075
<i>No, it's...</i>

05:37.075 --> 05:40.862
<i>I feel like...</i>

05:40.862 --> 05:44.256
You don't want to see me?

05:44.256 --> 05:48.173
<i>Like, sometimes I like
to just focus on your voice</i>

05:48.173 --> 05:53.440
<i>and your words without that
distracting face of yours.</i>

05:53.440 --> 05:55.267
Yeah, right.

06:01.404 --> 06:02.884
<i>I love this instead.</i>

06:02.884 --> 06:06.017
<i>We--
we actually see each other.</i>

06:06.017 --> 06:09.630
Yeah, sure.
Just swing on by, why don't you?

06:12.284 --> 06:15.940
<i>I mean, don't just think
we should meet someday?</i>

06:18.378 --> 06:20.249
No.

06:22.556 --> 06:25.559
it's part of the charm
of this relationship, Eric.

06:25.559 --> 06:27.909
The vast distance
that separates us.

06:33.480 --> 06:37.832
<i>I don't know.
It just doesn't feel right.</i>

06:37.832 --> 06:43.577
<i>I'd love to meet and
be in the same room with you.</i>

06:53.804 --> 06:55.676
I have to go to sleep.

06:59.854 --> 07:01.377
<i>- Anna.</i>
- This is me

07:01.377 --> 07:03.510
blowing you a kiss.

07:15.913 --> 07:18.525
So, I have two
open houses tomorrow,

07:18.525 --> 07:20.744
and then Tim and I are going
to meet with the caterers

07:20.744 --> 07:22.703
for the engagement party.

07:25.706 --> 07:28.665
But-- hi.
- Cool, cool.

07:28.665 --> 07:31.712
Um, I wanted to get back in time
to maybe do, like,

07:31.712 --> 07:34.454
a little birthday thingy
with you before you

07:34.454 --> 07:35.803
and the girls head out, okay?

07:35.803 --> 07:38.458
Thank you.

07:41.504 --> 07:44.638
Uh, also,
we have to sit down

07:44.638 --> 07:48.337
and formalize those college
tour dates, babe.

07:51.514 --> 07:53.211
Honey?

07:53.211 --> 07:55.779
Definitely.

07:55.779 --> 07:57.825
Girl.

07:59.435 --> 08:01.176
Let's go.

08:08.836 --> 08:11.534
- Hey.
<i>- Hey.</i>

08:11.534 --> 08:14.668
I was starting to think
you were ghosting me.

08:14.668 --> 08:18.498
No, no, I got--
got a little lost.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.761
What do you mean?

08:20.761 --> 08:23.154
I don't know where I am.

08:23.154 --> 08:25.505
I mean, I'll turn the camera
around, I'll show you.

08:25.505 --> 08:29.334
Pretty sure I can't help you,
but okay?

08:29.334 --> 08:30.858
No?

08:30.858 --> 08:32.816
What do you think?

09:26.870 --> 09:28.263
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

09:30.961 --> 09:33.181
Do you realize
how inappropriate

09:33.181 --> 09:35.052
and aggressive this is?

09:35.052 --> 09:36.967
<i>Yeah.</i>
Um, I'm sorry.

09:36.967 --> 09:40.057
<i>I-I-I...</i>

09:40.057 --> 09:44.888
<i>I guess
I thought it was a big</i>

09:44.888 --> 09:47.891
<i>gesture, but....</i>

09:47.891 --> 09:53.505
<i>Yes, a big, dumb gesture.</i>

09:53.505 --> 09:55.246
Yeah.

09:56.683 --> 10:00.121
<i>Shit.
I'm sorry.</i>

10:00.121 --> 10:02.123
What?

10:04.299 --> 10:07.694
<i>Look, um,
I have gifts for you.</i>

10:07.694 --> 10:11.611
<i>I'll just-- I'll leave it on
the porch, okay?</i>

10:14.396 --> 10:18.618
<i>Sh-- Sorry.</i>

10:18.618 --> 10:20.707
No, hold on.

10:20.707 --> 10:22.665
Uh, just-- just wait.

10:33.676 --> 10:35.156
Hi.

10:38.420 --> 10:41.379
Um...

10:41.379 --> 10:43.686
I have no interest in--
in coming in.

10:43.686 --> 10:46.036
I just--
I wanted to give you that.

10:51.476 --> 10:53.740
Happy birthday.

10:56.960 --> 10:59.528
Okay.

10:59.528 --> 11:02.487
Um, no, you know what?
Actually, I, um...

11:02.487 --> 11:05.273
One more thing, and then--
and then I'll go.

11:05.273 --> 11:09.712
You are even prettier
in person.

11:12.889 --> 11:16.197
Um, and um,
I'm going to go now.

11:16.197 --> 11:20.505
Um, I'm sorry if I
freaked you out.

11:20.505 --> 11:22.246
I'm an idiot.

11:22.246 --> 11:24.509
It's really dumb.

11:24.509 --> 11:26.686
Um...

11:26.686 --> 11:29.514
Call me later if you--

11:29.514 --> 11:31.516
if you like it.

12:15.256 --> 12:19.434
<i>"Her life had stood
a loaded gun.</i>

12:19.434 --> 12:24.178
<i>In corners till a day
the owner passed</i>

12:24.178 --> 12:28.008
<i>identified and carried me away."</i>

12:47.810 --> 12:51.248
How old are you, actually?

12:51.248 --> 12:52.859
28.

12:52.859 --> 12:56.427
Jesus.

12:56.427 --> 12:59.430
I'm not in college.

12:59.430 --> 13:06.089
I was, but
I dropped out a while ago.

13:06.089 --> 13:07.656
I have a lot of questions.

13:07.656 --> 13:10.398
And I just want to be straight

13:10.398 --> 13:12.356
with you
about everything.

13:12.356 --> 13:14.619
- That's thoughtful of you.
- Look.

13:17.231 --> 13:19.276
When we first met--
- Met?

13:19.276 --> 13:20.843
Eric, I met you, like,
half an hour ago.

13:20.843 --> 13:25.021
Okay, fine.
When we...

13:25.021 --> 13:32.028
When we first, you know,
got to know each other...

13:32.028 --> 13:36.119
I knew how special you were,
and-- and I--

13:36.119 --> 13:38.687
I panicked.

13:38.687 --> 13:41.864
You mean you lied?

13:41.864 --> 13:43.083
Yeah.

13:45.346 --> 13:47.478
Why did you panic?

13:49.872 --> 13:54.529
I mean, you're so
incredibly smart

13:54.529 --> 13:59.360
and you're funny
and you're kind and caring.

13:59.360 --> 14:01.884
You're like
1,000,001 other things,

14:01.884 --> 14:04.278
and I just--

14:04.278 --> 14:06.149
I knew I didn't want
to lose something

14:06.149 --> 14:08.369
with so much potential.

14:10.719 --> 14:13.678
Hey. Could you be there
at 4:30 today?

14:13.678 --> 14:16.420
I need help with the ribbons.

14:16.420 --> 14:18.074
<i>Ribbons?</i>

14:18.074 --> 14:20.903
Yeah, it's a thing we do.
It's ironic.

14:20.903 --> 14:23.166
<i>Is it now?</i>

14:23.166 --> 14:26.953
Yeah, 75% ironic.

14:28.868 --> 14:34.743
Well, congrats on your big,
dumb gesture.

14:34.743 --> 14:37.964
Well, you know, big and dumb
or go home, right?

14:45.232 --> 14:48.191
Thank you for the book.

14:48.191 --> 14:49.758
It was one of the most
thoughtful gifts

14:49.758 --> 14:51.760
anyone's ever given me.

14:55.068 --> 14:56.808
I'm glad.

15:07.428 --> 15:11.040
Um, okay.

15:11.040 --> 15:12.563
No.

15:12.563 --> 15:15.610
No, there's no way
I'm not getting a hug.

15:21.529 --> 15:23.835
Oh, man.

15:23.835 --> 15:26.099
Why?

15:26.099 --> 15:30.059
Why does your hair
smell so good?

15:35.847 --> 15:36.979
Jesus.

15:36.979 --> 15:38.981
I...

15:38.981 --> 15:40.287
I have to go.

15:40.287 --> 15:41.810
- Yeah, you do.
- Yeah.

15:50.036 --> 15:52.342
Babe.

15:52.342 --> 15:54.954
It's an ironic hat
and you have to wear it.

15:54.954 --> 15:56.520
It's a rule.

15:56.520 --> 15:58.218
- Where's the birthday girl at?
- I don't know.

15:58.218 --> 16:00.394
And the girl should be here
any minute to pick her up.

16:00.394 --> 16:01.786
Anna!

16:06.443 --> 16:08.837
Hey.

16:08.837 --> 16:10.447
- Oh, shit.
- What?

16:10.447 --> 16:13.320
Uh, my mom's home.
We fell asleep.

16:13.320 --> 16:14.799
Wait, what? What?

16:14.799 --> 16:16.410
Uh, you have to get dressed.

16:16.410 --> 16:18.107
- Oh, shit.
- Fast.

16:18.107 --> 16:20.327
Oh, shit.

16:20.327 --> 16:21.806
Uh...
- Shirt?

16:21.806 --> 16:24.592
Where's my shirt?
Where's my-- my shirt?

16:24.592 --> 16:27.682
- Anna?
- Hold on.

16:27.682 --> 16:29.031
Um, no, you have to hide.

16:29.031 --> 16:30.772
- What?
- Hide.

16:30.772 --> 16:33.383
Anna?

16:33.383 --> 16:35.255
Huh? Honey?
- Hold on.

16:35.255 --> 16:36.996
Don't.
Don't you knock?

16:36.996 --> 16:41.478
Sorry.
I thought you said come in.

16:41.478 --> 16:44.177
Um, I have something
for you downstairs.

16:44.177 --> 16:45.830
And the girls
are almost here, so...

16:45.830 --> 16:48.268
Yeah.
No, I'm sorry I snapped.

16:48.268 --> 16:51.010
I'm sorry I barged in.

16:51.010 --> 16:54.361
No, I fell asleep.
I'm just grumpy.

16:54.361 --> 16:55.710
No big deal.

16:55.710 --> 16:57.494
I'll be out soon.
- Okay.

17:00.323 --> 17:02.543
Oh.

17:02.543 --> 17:04.197
That's what?

17:04.197 --> 17:07.591
I don't know how I'm going
to get you out of here.

17:07.591 --> 17:10.855
- What do you mean?
- My mom and Tim are home.

17:12.814 --> 17:14.207
Uh, the window?

17:14.207 --> 17:15.512
Doesn't open wide enough
for a body.

17:15.512 --> 17:16.861
I've tried.

17:16.861 --> 17:19.038
I...

17:19.038 --> 17:20.778
I can't stay here.
- You have to.

17:20.778 --> 17:22.693
No, I can't.

17:22.693 --> 17:24.826
Okay, then let's go out there
and have Tim arrest you.

17:28.656 --> 17:30.745
Tim's a cop?

17:30.745 --> 17:32.703
Assistant chief of police.

17:32.703 --> 17:34.140
What?

17:37.621 --> 17:39.449
Is my head still intact?

17:41.451 --> 17:43.236
Yeah, I think so.

17:43.236 --> 17:44.802
'Cause she nearly bit it off.

17:52.027 --> 17:54.073
Birthday girl!

17:56.162 --> 17:58.816
- I won't be out late.
- No, I can't.

17:58.816 --> 18:00.166
I can't stay
in your house.

18:00.166 --> 18:02.777
I'll make it as quick as I can.
I promise.

18:02.777 --> 18:05.127
- Anna?!
- Coming!

18:05.127 --> 18:07.521
Please, just stay here.

18:07.521 --> 18:09.436
I'll be back soon, okay?

18:09.436 --> 18:11.481
I want to see you later.

18:17.270 --> 18:18.445
You promise?

18:18.445 --> 18:19.489
Yeah.

18:24.799 --> 18:34.243
♪ Happy birthday, dear Anna

18:36.419 --> 18:41.946
♪ Happy birthday to you

18:41.946 --> 18:43.818
Thank you.

18:43.818 --> 18:45.211
Uh...

18:48.344 --> 18:50.651
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you, Mom.

18:50.651 --> 18:53.349
- Happy birthday.
- Wow, you too?

18:53.349 --> 18:55.960
Yeah, well,
apparently it's tradition?

18:55.960 --> 18:58.180
- Okay, well, we should...

18:58.180 --> 18:59.268
- Yeah, we have to go.
- Oh, wait.

18:59.268 --> 19:01.488
No, no, no, okay?

19:01.488 --> 19:04.055
I baked this vegan cake
from scratch.

19:04.055 --> 19:07.015
I know you don't like sweets,
but you have to at least try it.

19:07.015 --> 19:08.756
Okay, one bite
and then we'll go--

19:10.149 --> 19:12.542
-  That's good.
- You like it?

19:12.542 --> 19:14.022
- Mm-hmm.
- Bye.

19:14.022 --> 19:15.241
- Let's go.
- Bye, thank you.

19:15.241 --> 19:16.285
- It was good.
- She liked it.

19:16.285 --> 19:17.721
In one bite, she liked it.

19:21.334 --> 19:23.945
Denny, what's up?

19:25.686 --> 19:28.036
Hey.

19:28.036 --> 19:30.038
Oh, my God.

19:30.038 --> 19:31.605
Look.

19:31.605 --> 19:33.215
Denny.
- Yeah.

19:33.215 --> 19:37.132
So happy birthday, I guess.

19:37.132 --> 19:38.568
Um...

19:38.568 --> 19:41.180
Brit, who apparently is a liar,

19:41.180 --> 19:46.489
told me you wouldn't
be here, so...

19:46.489 --> 19:48.012
Thank you, Denny.

19:48.012 --> 19:50.885
Yeah.
Um, okay.

19:50.885 --> 19:53.061
Alright, uh, bye.

19:53.061 --> 19:54.584
I'll see you--
I'll see you later.

19:54.584 --> 19:56.151
Bye.

19:56.151 --> 19:58.240
- Bye, Denny.
- Stop.

19:58.240 --> 20:01.112
- Stop, that was so sweet.
- He is so cute.

20:01.112 --> 20:02.679
Oh.

20:19.870 --> 20:21.394
Yeah.

20:21.394 --> 20:22.917
You know I want to.

20:22.917 --> 20:25.180
Well, you have the pool.

20:25.180 --> 20:26.921
You have Hailey's room,
which could be for Anna,

20:26.921 --> 20:29.010
which is criminally large.

20:29.010 --> 20:31.752
We got the gym in the basement.

20:33.536 --> 20:35.669
You know, it's funny, right?

20:35.669 --> 20:38.237
You sold it to me, and now I'm
trying to sell it back.

20:38.237 --> 20:40.848
Yeah, well, I know where
all that asbestos is hidden.

20:46.593 --> 20:51.554
I just hesitate to leave
this place, you know?

20:51.554 --> 20:53.382
After Gary left,
we floated around

20:53.382 --> 20:57.212
to some shitty situations,

20:57.212 --> 21:03.740
and this is the first place
that's felt like home.

21:03.740 --> 21:06.265
I get it.

21:06.265 --> 21:07.918
I do.

21:27.895 --> 21:30.550
Hey, birthday girl, what you
doing on your phone?

21:44.477 --> 21:46.435
Hey, lady, you want
to join your birthday party?

21:46.435 --> 21:49.743
Sorry. It's just-- it's just
my mom checking in on us.

21:49.743 --> 21:51.527
Oh, God.

21:51.527 --> 21:53.486
Tim and her are like
my relationship goals.

21:53.486 --> 21:55.139
- Yeah.
- Love you.

21:55.139 --> 21:57.054
- You, too.
- You, too?

21:57.054 --> 21:58.708
What kind of shit is that.

21:58.708 --> 22:00.623
- What do you mean?
- You, too?

22:00.623 --> 22:02.103
- I love you.
- That's what I thought.

22:15.899 --> 22:18.337
Are you going
to call Tim Dad?

22:18.337 --> 22:21.427
No. I think that ship
sailed a long time ago.

22:21.427 --> 22:23.429
Your dad ever call you
on your birthday?

22:23.429 --> 22:25.735
No, I haven't spoken to him
since I was four,

